We’re a unique startup in the tech sector looking to shake up the industry, and we really need your help. To sweeten the pot, we offer many perks. If you’re a self-starting go-getter with an ambitious spirit, keep reading.





ABOUT THE COMPANY


Access (that’s us) works with everyone from founders, to tech startups, to investors, and even with enterprises to bring their visions to life, however large or complex those visions may be. Add to that the suite of data-driven products we are developing to revolutionize and standardize the way innovation can happen, and you have almost covered everything we do. Yes, we’re innovating upon innovation itself… cool, right?




[Insert hilarious meme to show you how cool we are!]




Even though we are still building, we are already seeing absurdly high growth in one of our flagship products, AccessTeams™. It’s an SaaS product that offers organizations access to their own stacked team of dedicated, hand-picked, top talent.




We are transforming how work gets done, how innovation happens, and how innovators succeed, 
at scale
.




Anyone who is eager to drive change in the innovation economy should consider Access. Our data-driven products empower users across the global innovation ecosystem. From data &amp; analytics to tools for everyday management, Access' mission is to create a new standard for supporting founders, investors, startups, teams, and talent in order to unleash their full potential.





ABOUT THE JOB/POSITION


The environment in which we work is fast-paced, results-driven, and forward-thinking. To make an impact, our ideal candidate (you?) would work well in these conditions.




You would be working directly alongside our CEO, learning all the inner workings of Access. The idea here is that you are ambitious, looking to advance your career to eventually become a COO or other high-ranking official within the organization.




Due to the hands-on nature of this position, remote-only is not an option. You would need to be located in the Vancouver/Burnaby, BC area, or be willing to relocate.




This position will be highly demanding, but the rewards will reflect this. While we will be asking a lot of you, we want to assure you that, in return, you will:


Boost your career quickly;

Partner with people who are equally concerned with quality and speed;

Have a tangible, measurable impact on our project management process;

Expand your role as we grow;

Receive all the support you need;

Have access to furthering educational opportunities (e-book allowance, all the software you need, a learning and development budget, regular one-on-one feedback sessions, etc);

Receive assistance with maintaining your physical and mental health (gym allowance, headspace account, flexible office hours, etc);

Be able to reach senior managers across the business, at any time;

Be able to work in a hybrid environment; and

Enjoy unlimited holidays.






ABOUT YOUR (POTENTIAL) ROLE


As an Operations Associate and Executive Assistant to the CEO, you would:


Report directly to the CEO;

Manage the CEO’s calendar;

Work with the CEO, board of directors, and investors directly;

Attend Strategic Partner meetings;

Organize Public Relations operations;

Develop and implement workflow processes designed to increase team efficiency;

Translate complex marketing, operations or product plans into tactical steps, understand and anticipate codependencies, delay risks, and manage/maintain processes, and work-streams for the business, marketing, and product teams;

Work cross-functionally with the Operations, Finance, Product, Engineering, Growth, Account Management, and Partnership teams to grow the business;

Schedule events; and

Assist in managing multiple teams.






ABOUT YOU


What makes you different from other applicants is:


Your attention to detail;

Your organizational skills;

Your time management skills;

Your clear and concise communication skills;

Your ability to think on your feet;

Your enthusiasm;

Your can-do attitude;

Your patience;

Your social and emotional intelligence;

Your superior mediation skills;

Your ability to keep calm in a crisis;

Your background in business and/or tech; and

Your self-motivation.






ABOUT YOUR SUCCESS


The impact of your success cannot be overstated. This is a full-time permanent position. This role will help shape not just the future of our organization, but also your place within it and your career trajectory. As a result, we really want to make sure the right candidate is selected. If you still think that’s you after reading everything above, we very much look forward to your submission.




We’re on a mission: to help innovators connect and scale.

Why you should work for AGF Steel


• Family business with a global presence;

• Dynamic and friendly working atmosphere, in a constantly growing business sector;

• Parking on site;

• Dental, complementary health, vision, life and invalidity insurance paid by the employer;

• Free employee assistance program;

• Corporate events.





Mandate


The Receptionist will be responsible for the answering of all incoming calls and ensuring that the customers are greeted in a polite and professional manner.





Main responsibilities


• Receive inbound calls and monitoring of the general mailbox;

• Sorting and distribution of daily mail, incoming and outgoing courier’s;

• Greeting of clients and other visitors;

• Sorting and filing of accounting related documents – receivables, payables, payroll;

• Special Projects;

• Issuing of purchase orders for bill of ladings and matching with invoices for purchases made by the equipment maintenance person;

• Assisting the Controller with various accounting related duties;

• Upkeep of leased equipment supplies (Xerox) and maintenance requirements;

• Support to all accounting staff, H&amp;S, Sales and Estimation;

• Other duties as assigned.





Qualifications/Skills


• Relevant experience in an office environment;

• Familiarity with Word and Excel;

• General understanding of accounting principals;

• Methodical approach to data compilation;

• Sense of discretion, initiative and autonomy;

• Ability to work under pressure;

• Good communication skills;

• Bilingual (French and English).

